data.text:
I recently bought a Graflex Crown Graphic. It came with about 17 film holders. Upon reviewing my purchase I discovered some of the wooden Lisco film holders still contained film! Now I know this camera has not been used in a long long time... atleast that's what the guy said. I went through them in the dark and set aside the ones with film. From the best my fingers could feel I can up with two different films. Below I made a simulation of what I feel the edges should look like. I'm wondering if anyone out there can help me to identify this film. Once I know what it is I can decide how to go about using/processing it. Granted they haven't been tamped with before that is. http://img267.imageshack.us/images/thpix.gif
You can also just shoot one and process it. Try rating it at iso 100 and process one. You can get a better idea after that. I would also pull a sheet out and look at the color of the Anti Halation backing. They are many different types and colors. It might help narrow it down. -ian
